Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring @water{1 1/2%cups} and @chicken stock concentrate{1} to a boil in a #small pot{}. Remove veins and seeds from @chili pepper{1}(deveined and seeded), then finely chop. Zest @Meyer lemon{1}, then cut into wedges. Trim @green beans{6%oz}. Chop @parsley{1/4%oz}. Roughly chop @walnuts{1%oz}. Once water is boiling, add @couscous{3/4%cup} to #pot. Cover and remove from heat.

With your hand on top of one @chicken breast{12%oz}, cut ¾ of the way, parallel to #cutting board{}, stopping before you slice through completely. Open it up like a book. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Repeat with other breast.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (use an ovenproof pan if you have one). Add chicken in a single layer and cook until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Transfer pan to oven and roast until chicken is no longer pink in center, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Transfer chicken to a baking dish first if your pan isn't ovenproof.

Heat a drizzle of oil in another large pan over medium heat. Add green beans. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, tossing, until lightly browned, about ~{5%minutes}. Add half the lemon zest and a big squeeze of lemon juice. Stir and let cook another ~{1-2%minutes}. Add walnuts and cook, tossing, until warmed through, about ~{1%minute}. Remove mixture from pan and set aside.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan. Add red chili (to taste) and cook, tossing, until soft, ~{2-3%minutes}. Pour in @water{3/4%cup} and bring to a simmer. Stir in @apricot jam{1%oz} and continue simmering until mixture is thick and sticky, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and lemon juice (start with a squeeze and add more as needed).

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}, then stir in parsley, remaining lemon zest, and a few squeezes of lemon juice. Slice chicken breast into strips. Divide couscous between plates, then top with chicken and green bean mixture. Drizzle glaze over chicken and serve.